From: Jay Vosburgh <jay.vosburgh@canonical.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Mar 2018 14:42:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] virtio-net: Fix operstate for virtio when no
 VIRTIO_NET_F_STATUS
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.16.13
Git-commit: bda7fab54828bbef2164bb23c0f6b1a7d05cc718

[ Upstream commit bda7fab54828bbef2164bb23c0f6b1a7d05cc718 ]

The operstate update logic will leave an interface in the
default UNKNOWN operstate if the interface carrier state never changes
from the default carrier up state set at creation.  This includes the
case of an explicit call to netif_carrier_on, as the carrier on to on
transition has no effect on operstate.

	This affects virtio-net for the case that the virtio peer does
not support VIRTIO_NET_F_STATUS (the feature that provides carrier state
updates).  Without this feature, the virtio specification states that
"the link should be assumed active," so, logically, the operstate should
be UP instead of UNKNOWN.  This has impact on user space applications
that use the operstate to make availability decisions for the interface.

	Resolve this by changing the virtio probe logic slightly to call
netif_carrier_off for both the "with" and "without" VIRTIO_NET_F_STATUS
cases, and then the existing call to netif_carrier_on for the "without"
case will cause an operstate transition.

